These is the install file for the Semantic Data Types extension.
	
Extension page on mediawiki.org: https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Extension:Semantic_Data_Types
Latest version of the install file: http://svn.wikimedia.org/viewvc/mediawiki/trunk/extensions/SemanticDataTypes/INSTALL?view=co


== Requirements ==

Semantic Data Types requires:

* MediaWiki 1.16 or above
* Semantic MediaWiki 1.6 or above
* PHP 5.2 or above

== Download ==

You can get the code directly from SVN. Tags can be obtained via

 svn checkout <nowiki>http://svn.wikimedia.org/svnroot/mediawiki/tags/extensions/SemanticDataTypes/REL_version</nowiki>

Where 'version' is the version number of the tag, such as 0_1 (see the [http://svn.wikimedia.org/svnroot/mediawiki/tags/extensions/SemanticDataTypes/ available tags]).
The latest code can be obtained from trunk:

 svn checkout <nowiki>http://svn.wikimedia.org/svnroot/mediawiki/trunk/extensions/SemanticDataTypes/</nowiki>

== Installation ==

Once you have downloaded the code, place the ''SemanticDataTypes'' directory within your MediaWiki
'extensions' directory. Then add the following code to your [[Manual:LocalSettings.php|LocalSettings.php]] file:

# Semantic Data Types
require_once( "$IP/extensions/SemanticDataTypes/SemanticDataTypes.php" );

== Configuration ==

Configuration of Semantic Data Types is done by assigning to $egSDTSettings in your
[[Manual:LocalSettings.php|LocalSettings.php]] file, AFTER the inclusion of the
extension. The options are listed below and their default is set in the Contest settings file:
http://svn.wikimedia.org/viewvc/mediawiki/trunk/extensions/SemanticDataTypes/SemanticDataTypes.settings.php?view=markup
You should NOT modify the settings file, but can have a look at it to get an idea of
how to use the settings, in case the below descriptions do not suffice.

